02-22 08:37:07.369 I/flutter (19005): 
02-22 08:37:07.369 I/flutter (19005): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:37:07.369 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:07.369 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:37:10.398 I/flutter (19005): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:37:10.398 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:10.398 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:37:14.473 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:37:15.506 I/flutter (19005): 
02-22 08:37:15.506 I/flutter (19005): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:37:15.507 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:15.507 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:37:17.538 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:17.538 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. 02-22 08:37:19.565 I/flutter (19005): 
02-22 08:37:19.565 I/flutter (19005): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:37:19.565 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:19.565 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:37:21.597 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:37:22.618 I/flutter (19005): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:37:22.618 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:22.618 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:37:25.663 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:25.663 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. 02-22 08:37:28.717 I/flutter (19005): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:37:28.718 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:28.718 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:37:29.740 I/flutter (19005): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:37:29.740 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:29.740 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:37:31.763 I/flutter (19005): 
02-22 08:37:31.763 I/flutter (19005): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:37:31.763 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:31.763 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:37:35.840 I/flutter (19005): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:37:35.840 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:35.840 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:37:36.859 I/flutter (19005): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:37:36.859 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:36.859 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:37:37.875 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:37:38.891 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:37:40.929 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:37:40.929 I/flutter (19005): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. 02-22 08:37:45.986 I/flutter (19005): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.

02-22 08:45:06.997 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:06.997 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:09.030 I/flutter (19882): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:45:09.030 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:09.030 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:11.049 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:11.049 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:14.091 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:45:16.129 I/flutter (19882): 
02-22 08:45:16.129 I/flutter (19882): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:45:16.129 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:16.129 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:18.167 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:18.167 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:19.199 I/flutter (19882): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:45:19.199 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:19.199 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:21.228 I/flutter (19882): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:45:21.228 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:21.229 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:23.262 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:23.262 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:25.293 I/flutter (19882): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:45:25.293 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:25.293 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:26.323 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. 02-22 08:45:28.354 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:28.354 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:29.379 I/flutter (19882): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:45:29.380 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:29.380 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:31.406 I/flutter (19882): 
02-22 08:45:31.406 I/flutter (19882): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:45:31.406 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:31.406 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:32.431 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:32.431 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. 02-22 08:45:33.451 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:33.451 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:35.478 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:45:36.500 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:45:37.516 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:37.516 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. 02-22 08:45:38.533 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:38.533 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. 02-22 08:45:39.549 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:39.549 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:41.583 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:45:43.609 I/flutter (19882): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:45:43.609 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:43.609 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:45.647 I/flutter (19882): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:45:45.647 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:45:47.660 I/flutter (19882): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:48:52.171 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:48:52.171 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:48:54.207 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:48:54.207 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:48:56.245 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:48:56.245 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:48:59.269 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:49:01.311 I/flutter (20650): 
02-22 08:49:01.312 I/flutter (20650): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:49:01.312 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:01.312 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:49:04.383 I/flutter (20650): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:49:04.383 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:04.383 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:49:06.420 I/flutter (20650): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:49:06.420 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:06.420 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:49:08.453 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:08.453 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:49:10.485 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:10.485 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:49:11.516 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:49:13.546 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:13.546 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:49:14.571 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:14.572 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:49:16.599 I/flutter (20650): 
02-22 08:49:16.599 I/flutter (20650): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:49:16.599 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:16.599 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:49:17.625 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:49:20.671 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:20.671 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. 02-22 08:49:21.688 I/flutter (20650): Anti-Gravity detectou um problema: The showSnackBar() method cannot be called during build.
02-22 08:49:21.688 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:21.688 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:49:22.709 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:22.709 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. 02-22 08:49:23.731 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:23.732 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. 02-22 08:49:24.751 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:24.751 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. Otherwise, you can also schedule a post-frame callback using SchedulerBinding.addPostFrameCallback to show the snack bar after the current frame.

02-22 08:49:28.819 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:28.819 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead. 02-22 08:49:30.855 I/flutter (20650): The showSnackBar() method was called during build, which is prohibited as showing snack bars requires updating state. Updating state is not possible during build.
02-22 08:49:30.855 I/flutter (20650): Instead of calling showSnackBar() during build, call it directly in your on tap (and related) callbacks. If you need to immediately show a snack bar, make the call in initState() or didChangeDependencies() instead.
